        <div>
          <h2 id="ce1"><u>Explanation</u></h2>
          <p>In the Cosmic Era, the Earth is orbited by several space colonies called “Productive Location Ally on Nexus Technology” or PLANTS, whose inhabitants are known as coordinators, test tube super babies, genetically enhanced to human perfection. They do not get along well with the natural humans still on Earth, to the point of nuking each other, until the PLANTS' military arm, the “Zodiac Alliance Freedom Treaty” or ZAFT, invented technologies that prevent nuclear reactions from occurring. ZAFT also invented battery-powered Mobile Suits which led them to dominate the earth alliance in the war until the federation secretly develops Mobile Suits of their own.</p>
          <p>Hidden in a neutral space colony, these new Mobile Suits possess special armor technology that makes them impervious to physical damage. ZAFT finds out about this and attempts to steal them but a teenage student, Kira Yamato ends up taking control of one, the Strike and is forcibly conscripted into the earth alliance military.</p>
          <p>Turns out, Kira is himself a coordinator and his childhood friend, Athrun Zala, is piloting one of the stolen Gundam. The conflicts as a whole are made very personal, it's not just a kid thrust into a war he didn't sign up for, it is Kira being forced to fight his friend, Athrun, and their challenges and reconciling their places, being both friends and unwitting enemies as they kill each other’s other friends. It's also Kira dealing with the fact that he's working for a military where people hate him as he is a coordinator.</p>
          <p>SEED is kind of the ultimate realization of the ethos and philosophy that led to the Wing Gundam, taking character-driven melodramatic hyperreality and then injecting it into the core narrative arc of the series. Don’t even get started on Gundam SEED Destiny, Gundam SEED Destiny is even more divisive even among fans of SEED.</p>

          <h4><u>Personal Thoughts</u></h4>
          <p>If you're looking for harder science fiction and the more grounded Mecca action that the rest of Gundam is known for, this might not be for you. On the other hand, if what you want is an anime character drama couched in a lot of pretty lasers blasting into space, try giving this series a try.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="container-information-adjust-divider">
          <h2 id="ce2">Characters</h2>

          <h3>Kira Yamato</h3>
          <img class="ce_pic" src="image/Kira_71.png" alt="Kira_71.png">
          <p>Kira Yamato (キラ・ヤマト) is the main protagonist of Mobile Suit Gundam SEED and the main protagonist of the second half of Mobile Suit Gundam SEED Destiny. Kira is the adopted son of Caridad Yamato and is Cagalli Yula Athha's twin brother. He pilots the GAT-X105 Strike Gundam, the ZGMF-X10A Freedom Gundam, and the ZGMF-X20A Strike Freedom Gundam.</p>
          <p>Kira has a dislike of war and conflict, he is more than willing to fight if it means protecting his friends and loved ones. As the series progresses, Kira becomes traumatized by the people he has killed and the ones he failed to protect, showing that he is atychiphobic (afraid of failure) and resulting in him to becoming obsessed with protecting the Archangel.By the Second Alliance-PLANT War, Kira's overall personality is calmer, mature, and philosophical. He has gained respect from soldiers in Orb's military due to his piloting skills and being the brother of Orb's ruler.</p>
          <p>Kira has a sharp sense and rapid information processing ability; He is shown to have great adaptability through his constant improvement of the Strike Gundam's incomplete OS to enhance its performance to match with the combat situation he faces. Kira has exceptional mobile suit shooting precision which has became the core of his piloting style after acquiring the ZGMF-X10A Freedom Gundam. By the end of the Second Alliance-PLANT War, Kira was able to singlehandedly shot down all of the DRAGOONs from the Legend Gundam.</p>
          <p>While lacking any true form of military training, Kira's fighting ability developed quickly and greatly as his time in combat increases, along with his mastery of SEED mode. In contrast to his piloting capabilities, Kira is shown to be inexperienced with handguns, preferring not to use them, as shown when he throws a gun at an assailant during a terrorist attack instead of firing it. By the Second Alliance-PLANT War, however, his handgun skills have improved significantly seen in the second assassination attempt on Lacus Clyne at Copernicus City on the Moon.</p>

          <div class="button-container">
