          <h3>ORB-01 Akatsuki Gundam</h3>
          <img class="ce_pic" src="image/Akatsuki-front.png" alt="Akatsuki-front.png">
          <img class="ce_pic" src="image/Akatsuki-rear.jpg" alt="Akatsuki-rear.jpg">
          <img class="ce_pic" src="image/shiranui.jpg" alt="shiranui.jpg">
          <img class="ce_pic_square" src="image/owashi.jpg" alt="owashi.jpg">
          <p>The ORB-01 Akatsuki Gundam is a Mobile Suit introduced in the anime Mobile Suit Gundam SEED Destiny. It is initially piloted by Cagalli Yula Athha using the "Oowashi" Sky Pack, and later by Mu La Flaga using the "Shiranui" Space Pack.</p>
          <h4>Technology & Combat Characteristics</h4>
          <p>The Akatsuki Gundam was developed through the fusion of the knowledge that the Orb engineers had gained from studying the Strike Gundam and its Striker Pack support system, with newer Orb-based prototype technologies. Its most remarkable feature is its gold-colored armor. This armor is actually a mirror surface armor which is able to deflect, making the mobile suit virtually impervious to beam shots. However, its vulnerability to melee and physical weapons remained equal to that of any other mobile suit, hence the presence of a shield as part of its armaments. Its standard armaments include a twin beam saber, head-mounted CIWS, an arm-mounted shield, and a beam rifle. </p>
          <p>The Akatsuki can also equip two optional backpacks, which are derived from the Strike Gundam's Striker Packs. On Earth, it can use an aerial backpack known as "Oowashi", granting it atmospheric flight capabilities. The backpack is armed with two beam cannons, the Oowashi can separate from the mobile suit and transform into a support aircraft. When operating in space, the Akatsuki uses the other backpack called the "Shiranui". This backpack increases the suit's mobility and was equiped with seven remote control beam turret units that have offensive and defensive capabilities.</p>
